If you run a meetup or are aware of a group of people meeting and discussing Emacs, please add them here so other people can connect.

Meeting other Emacs geeks is a great way to pick up ideas and learn even more. Can't find an Emacs meetup near you? [http://harryrschwartz.com/2015/09/14/starting-an-emacs-meetup.html Here are a few tips on starting an Emacs meetup]. Have fun!

== Upcoming events ==

* [https://www.meetup.com/New-York-Emacs-Meetup/events/274356205/ Dec 7, 2020 7pm-9pm EST: EmacsNYC: Literate Programming with Org Mode (virtual)]
* [https://www.emacs-doctor.com/emacs-paris-user-group/ Dec 8, 2020 17:30h to 19h CET: Paris, France (virtual)]
* [https://www.meetup.com/emacs-ffm/ Dec 16, 2020 8pm-10pm GMT+1: Frankfurt, Germany (virtual) - creating our own major mode]
* [https://emacs-berlin.org/ Dec 30, 2020 18:30 CET: Emacs Berlin]

You can also add this [https://calendar.google.com/calendar/ical/c_rkq3fc6u8k1nem23qegqc90l6c%40group.calendar.google.com/public/basic.ics ical feed] to your calendar. 

